  m_Name: Forepaw_Dewclaw_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Dewclaw_R
  partName: Forepaw Dewclaw Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right forepaw dewclaw is a reduced digit positioned higher on the inner side
    of the canine forelimb. Although it may not contact the ground during normal
    locomotion, the dewclaw contributes to stability, traction, and grip during rapid
    turns, climbing, or grasping movements.
  - Tendons and ligaments associated with the dewclaw allow limited motion and provide
    additional support to the carpal region during dynamic activities. The claw also
    assists in holding objects and maintaining balance on uneven terrain.
